0.user_question: While shopping, Maria bought 35 green towels and 21 white towels. If she gave her mother 34 of them, how many towels did Maria end up with?

ost_step.1: Add the number of green towels and white towels Maria originally bought to get the total number of towels. She bought 35 green towels and 21 white towels, so she had 35 + 21 = 56 towels in total.
ost_step.2: Subtract the number of towels she gave her mother from the total number of towels. She gave away 34 towels. Thus, she ended up with 56 (total towels) - 34 (towels given to her mother) = 22 towels.
